The paper discusses the Vapnik-Chervonenkis dimension, which is a fundamental concept in machine learning theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also touches upon combinatorial structures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper discusses measurability issues, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
